// JIT kernel: reading globals inside a hot loop (OP_GETTABUP).
//
// A global read compiles to ULOAD (fetch the _ENV upvalue table) + GETTABUP,
// which the codegen lowers exactly like GETFIELD: an inline hash-slot search of
// _ENV for the constant short-string key (gen_hash_find, walking the collision
// chain) followed by a value-type guard and load. The value type is predicted
// at record time from the live global and guarded at run time, so reassigning a
// global to a different type side-exits; an absent global (chain end) also
// side-exits. GETTABUP is not RA-safe, so these traces run with register
// allocation disabled (values in spill slots) -- still far faster than the
// interpreter. This mixes an int global, a float global, and an expression that
// combines them, so both the int and float GETTABUP value paths are exercised.
gi = 7;
gf = 2.5;
gi2 = 3;
int si = 0;
float sf = 0.0;
for (int rep = 0, 4000) {
  for (int j = 0, 15) {
    si = si + gi * gi2;
    sf = sf + gf;
  }
}
print(si);
print(sf);
